The BIG GIVE Back (May, 2016)
AmCap was a title sponsor at the 24-hour BIG GIVE Houston and BIG GIVE San Antonio events last month. In a joint effort with SNAP, an organization whose mission is prevent the suffering and death of cats and dogs due to overpopulation and preventable diseases, raised $20,000!




 





 















 



 
 

 




 
Touchdown Crawfish Style (May, 2016)
AmCap donated water and lent out tents for a crawfish boil to benefit the Waltrip High School football team. Division Vice President Chris Parrish of the Hope Tree branch, was at the reins as the crawfish chef, and delighted and wooed the participants by the mouthful – literally! 




 













 



 
 
 




 
Funding the Future (April, 2016)
AmCap proudly sponsored Green Eco Builders during the latest Circuit of the Americas race in Austin, Texas. A 16-hour race (eight on Saturday, eight on Sunday), it was both a challenge and a thrill. Green Eco Builders finished 3rd on Saturday despite colliding with a spinning car in front of their race car. The damage to the car was so severe, driver changes had to occur through the car window, due to the door being smashed shut. “We were running well mid-way through Sunday, when we blew out our motor,” said George Kopecky, founder of Green Eco Builders. “Oh well, that’s racing!”



Georger Kopecky with the drivers of the 16 our race.






 
Helping Others Reach New Heights (April, 2016)
AmCap showed their support by sponsoring the Northland Christian Volleyball team, helping them in their dedication and commitment to achieving their goals. The mission of the Northland Volleyball program is to serve God through the pursuit of playing volleyball at the highest level possible.

  





 
Keeping it Clean (April, 2016)
AMCAP is an official highway sponsor.





 



















 





 

 




 
Dedication Through Service (April, 2016)
Success smelled super sweet at the 4th Annual BBQ & Crawfish Boil, a joint project between AmCap, AmCap Hope Tree and AmCap Premier. A huge thank you goes out to all the volunteers that tirelessly worked to serve over 600 people! Organizer Chris Parrish stated, “We are always proud to work for a company that supports our community involvement and encourages us to celebrate company wide.”




 





































 



 
 




 




 
Building a Better Future (March, 2016)
AmCap’s own Maria Salazar, Connie Chambers and Julia Null participated in EllieCares’ employee-run volunteer program. Together with the Patrick Kelley Youth Foundation, EllieCares assembles bicycles for underprivileged and at-risk Las Vegas children.




 































 



 
 



 




 
Donate for Date Night (January, 2016)

Major Mortgage donated dozens of toys to the Salvation Army this Christmas thanks to a clever incentive giving employees the chance to win a gift card to one of four local eateries for each toy donated and, of course, the kind generosity of their entire team.




 
AmCap Toy Drive (December, 2015)
AmCap collected a total of $6,415 in donations from employees and spent it at numerous stores, including Walmart, Ross, Toys R Us and Target. We purchased just over 500 items in total, which we donated to four Houston area charities and one deserving family.




 



















 



 
 








 
Partnering to Make a Big Difference (November, 2015)

AmCap co-sponsored last November’s IMG Financial Group Charity Golf Classic Tournament, benefitting The Folds of Honor Foundation, an organization that provides scholarships and financial assistance to the children and families of those killed or disabled while serving our country.




 
Racing for the Cure (October, 2015)

On October 4, 2015, members of the AmCap family joined with 25,000 other Houstonians to participate in the annual Race for the Cure event. Together with our community, we helped to raise more than $1 million for breast cancer treatment.




 
Habitat for Humanity

      AmCap has become a loyal partner of Habitat for Humanity. As an AmCap family, we are committed to donating funds and volunteer hours to build homes around the country for families in need.




 
V.A. Loan Program
AmCap recognizes the sacrifices our military heroes make. We offer quality loans to the men and women of the armed forces to ensure they have a place to call home when they return from duty.
To learn more about our V.A. Loan Program, contact the AmCap location nearest you.
“You have absolutely lived up to your reputation of operating in excellence. You have gone way above and beyond to make this happen for us, and we can't thank you enough for all you have done for our family and so many other veterans here in the great state of Texas. Please let us know if there is anything we can do for you in the future. We count it a blessing to have worked with the very best in the business. Thanks again!”
Will Witherspoon, Master Sergeant, USAF (ret.)
